ammar of the language, the author describes the process of developing an archivable textual corpus that is used to make example sentences citable and playable, using software (Audiamus) developed in the course of the research. An included DVD provides a dictionary and finderlist, a set of interlinearized example texts and elicited sentences, and playable media versions of most example sentences and of the example texts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Feb 2021) 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / Oceanic & Australian Languages.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHawaii eBook Package 2000-2013z978311056414340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082486125440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824861254423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780824861254.jpg  a978-3-11-056414-3  Hawaii eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles